    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>We propose to observe the CO(4-3) transition in the host galaxy of the dark GRB080207 at z=2.08, the only GRB host for which CO has been detected so far. Combined with our previous CO(3-2) measurement, we will determine for the very first time the gas excitation conditions in a GRB host. While the bulk of Long GRBs has been found in low-mass galaxies, the GRB080207 host is a highly star-forming and massive system which challenges our understanding of the possible effect of metallicity in the relationship between LGRBs and star formation. From comparison with field galaxies, we will examine if the gas consumption in this object is triggered by secular phenomena or starbursting processes. Our analysis will be a unique first test on whether probing high-redshift star formation by GRBs is biased by the dust-enshrouded dark bursts, and reveal if less-biased samples of LGRB hosts could shed a new light on the cosmic growth of structures.</prp:abstract>
